cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.CC 

This paper deals with regular languages and their complexity measures, which are typically studied in the field of formal language theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves the study of semigroups, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant as the paper discusses the size of the syntactic semigroup. The paper also involves the study of boolean operations, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and circuit complexity (cs.CC).
